Function Reference/get comment author « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve the author of the current comment. If the comment has an empty
comment\_author field, then 'Anonymous' person is assumed. This function
is meant to live inside of the WordPress loop.

Usage
-----

` <?php $author = get_comment_author( $comment_ID ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$comment_ID` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optionl*) The ID of the comment for which to retrieve the author.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   The comment author

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

Change Log
----------

Since: [1.5.0](/Version_1.5 "Version 1.5")

Source File
-----------

get\_comment\_author() is located in `wp-includes/comment-template.php`

